  "prompt": "What are the biggest frustrations that people have about their boyfriends?",
  "response": "Relationships can be incredibly rewarding, but they also come with challenges. Some common frustrations that people may have about their boyfriends include:\n\n1. **Lack of Communication**:  \n   - Not expressing feelings or thoughts clearly.  \n   - Avoiding important conversations or being dismissive.  \n\n2. **Emotional Unavailability**:  \n   - Struggling to open up or be vulnerable.  \n   - Not providing emotional support during difficult times.  \n\n3. **Inattentiveness or Thoughtlessness**:  \n   - Forgetting important dates or events.  \n   - Not showing appreciation or effort in the relationship.  \n\n4. **Different Priorities or Goals**:  \n   - Mismatched expectations about the future (e.g., marriage, children).  \n   - Spending too much time on work, hobbies, or friends instead of the relationship.  \n\n5. **Lack of Effort**:  \n   - Not contributing equally to household chores or responsibilities.  \n   - Failing to plan dates or make romantic gestures.  \n\n6. **Jealousy or Insecurity**:  \n   - Displaying distrust or questioning the partner's actions without reason.  \n\n7. **Conflict Resolution Issues**:  \n   - Avoiding arguments instead of addressing them.  \n   - Being defensive or unwilling to compromise.  \n\n8. **Bad Habits or Lifestyle Differences**:  \n   - Clashing over health, hygiene, or financial habits.  \n   - Different levels of cleanliness or organization.  \n\n9. **Ignoring Boundaries**:  \n   - Not respecting personal space or time.  \n   - Overstepping in areas like social media or privacy.  \n\n10. **Lack of Affection or Intimacy**:  \n    - Not showing physical affection or emotional closeness.  \n    - Different levels of interest in sexual intimacy.  \n\n11. **Being Overly Dependent or Independent**:  \n    - Relying too heavily on the partner for emotional or practical needs.  \n    - Acting distant or detached, making the partner feel unimportant.  \n\n12. **Unresolved Past Issues**:  \n    - Bringing baggage from previous relationships into the current one.  \n    - Not addressing personal insecurities or traumas that affect the relationship.  \n\nIt's important to note that these frustrations can often be resolved through open communication, mutual effort, and a willingness to work together. Every relationship has its ups and downs, and addressing these issues constructively can strengthen the bond between partners.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
